 ## Safety Mechanisms
+
+### Battery SOC Protection
+
+**Purpose**: Prevent FORCE_DISCHARGE mode when battery State of Charge (SOC) is critically low
+
+**Default Threshold**: 20% (configurable via `min_discharge_soc_percent`)
+
+**Range**: 10-80% (validates in JSON schema)
+
+**Enforcement**: Two-level protection system
+
+**Implementation**:
+```python
+def _check_battery_protection(self, target_mode: BatteryMode) -> tuple[bool, str | None]:
+    """Check if battery protection should block FORCE_DISCHARGE mode."""
+    if target_mode != BatteryMode.FORCE_DISCHARGE:
+        return False, None
+
+    threshold = self.daemon_config["daemon_settings"].get("min_discharge_soc_percent", 20)
+    soc_data = solax_modbus_soc(self.system_config)
+
+    if soc_data is None:
+        # Fail-safe: block if can't read SOC
+        return True, "Cannot read battery SOC - safety block"
+
+    master_soc = soc_data.get("master", 0)
+    slave_soc = soc_data.get("slave", 0)
+    min_soc = min(master_soc, slave_soc)
+
+    if min_soc <= threshold:
+        return True, f"SOC {min_soc}% at/below threshold {threshold}%"
+
+    return False, None
+```
+
+**Protection Levels**:
+1. **Preventive**: Checks before entering FORCE_DISCHARGE mode
+2. **Emergency**: Monitors during FORCE_DISCHARGE and exits if SOC drops to threshold
+
+**Override Behavior**: Switches to SELF_USE mode instead of blocking entirely
+
+**Rationale**:
+- Prevents deep discharge that could damage battery cells
+- Uses minimum of master and slave SOC (protects weakest battery)
+- Fail-safe: blocks FORCE_DISCHARGE if SOC cannot be read
+- Emergency exit prevents mid-cycle battery damage
 
