+### Why Battery SOC Protection?
+
+**Alternative**: Rely on inverter's built-in protection only
+
+**Chosen**: Add daemon-level SOC monitoring with configurable threshold
+
+**Rationale**:
+- **User Control**: Allows more conservative protection than inverter defaults (10%)
+- **Dual-Battery Safety**: Monitors both master and slave, protects weakest battery
+- **Fail-Safe**: Blocks FORCE_DISCHARGE if SOC cannot be read
+- **Graceful Degradation**: Switches to SELF_USE instead of hard blocking
+- **Emergency Exit**: Continuous monitoring exits FORCE_DISCHARGE if SOC drops mid-cycle
+- **Flexibility**: Configurable threshold (10-80%) for different use cases
 
+**Implementation Choice**: Two-level protection (preventive + emergency) ensures safety even if schedule calculation fails
+
+**Default 20%**: Conservative default provides 10% margin above hardware limit while still allowing useful discharge periods
+
